/*
 * This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to evaluate a condition based on an input argument.
 * It checks the boolean value of the "foo" argument. If true, it sets the value of the ".dest" node to "yup!".
 * The [if] slot is used to conditionally execute the [set-value] slot based on the value of the "foo" argument.
 */
.arguments
   bar:bool
.result
if
   get-value:x:@.arguments/*/bar
   .lambda
      set-value:x:@.result
         .:confirmed!